Present location: INSTITUT DE PAPYROLOGIE ET D'ÉGYPTOLOGIE, UNIVERSITÉ DE LILLE III [02/049] LILLE
Technique: ENAMELLED; ENGRAVED; PRESSED IN A FORM/MODEL
Name: Scarab
Description: Very crude small scarab whose head, clypeus, prothorax, elytra and legs are nonetheless well defined. The reversed is carved with two deeply carved signs, the reed leaf and the feather.
